{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode7T2|melody', 'text' : 'The same One.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode7T2|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8H|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8H|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8H|melody', 'text' : 'Heirmos.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8H|text', 'text' : 'This is it, the Day which is chosen and holy, * Day One of the Sabbaths. * It is the queen-day, the Lord's Day, * and the Feast of all feasts, * and the Festival above every festival, * on which we extol Christ and bless Him to the ages.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode81|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode81|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode81|melody', 'text' : 'This is it.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode81|text', 'text' : 'Come on this illustrious day of Resurrection and day of Christ's Kingdom, let us receive the communion of the joy divine from the new fruit of the vine, for eternal life, and highly extol Him as God unto the ages.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode82|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode82|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode82|melody', 'text' : 'This is it.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode82|text', 'text' : 'Lift up your eyes round about You and see, O Zion. Behold, like beacons shining with light divine have your children come to you from the West, from the North and from seaward and from the East. In you they extol Christ and bless Him to the ages.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode83|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode83|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode83|melody', 'text' : 'This is it.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode83|text', 'text' : 'Father, ruler over all, and Logos and Spirit, O Nature divine, in three Hypostases united, transcending essence and divinity, in You have we been baptized; we praise and bless and worship You, unto all the ages.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T1|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T1|melody', 'text' : 'This is it.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T1|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T2|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T2|melody', 'text' : 'This is it.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode8T2|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M01|text', 'text' : 'O my soul, magnify Him who willingly suffered, was buried, and arose from the grave on the third day.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M02|text', 'text' : 'O my soul, magnify Christ who is the Giver of life, and who rose from the grave on the third day.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M03|text', 'text' : 'Christ is the new Pascha, the sacrificial Victim, the Lamb of God that takes away the sin of the world.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M04|text', 'text' : 'Today creation all is exultant and rejoices, for Christ has arisen, and Hades was despoiled.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M05|text', 'text' : 'An Angel, bright and dazzling, appeared to the women; he said, "Now stop your weeping, for Christ the Lord has risen.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M06|text', 'text' : 'To the tomb of Christ, Mary Magdalene went running, and seeing Him she asked Him, as though he were the gardener.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M07|text', 'text' : 'You slept and then you wakened the dead of all the ages, for like a king you roared, as the Lion born of Judah.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M08|text', 'text' : 'O people, leap with great joy, for Christ the Lord has risen; by death He trampled death, and the dead He resurrected.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9M09|text', 'text' : 'Hades today was plundered by Christ the Lord and Savior, who raised all its prisoners, whom it had held in awful captivity forever.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9MTr|text', 'text' : 'O my soul, magnify the power of the Godhead, that is three hypostases and also undivided.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9MTh|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, blessed Virgin; rejoice, O glorified one. Rejoice, your Son has risen from the grave on the third day.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9MKa|text', 'text' : 'The Angel cried aloud to the Lady full of grace: Rejoice, O pure Virgin; and again I say Rejoice. Your Son has truly risen from the grave on the third day.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9H|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9H|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9H|melody', 'text' : 'Heirmos.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9H|text', 'text' : 'Be illumined, illumined, O New Jerusalem; * for the glory of the Lord has arisen over you. * Dance now for joy, O Zion, and exult. * And you be merry, O pure Theotokos, * at the arising of the One you bore.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode91|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode91|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode91|melody', 'text' : 'Be illumined.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode91|text', 'text' : 'Divine and beloved and sweetest utterance of Yours! * For You really and truly pledged that You will be with us * unto the end of the age, O Christ. * And we the faithful, clinging to Your promise, * our anchor of hope, rejoice.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode92|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode92|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode92|melody', 'text' : 'Be illumined.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode92|text', 'text' : 'O Pascha, the great and most sacred Passover, O Christ, * You the wisdom and Logos and the power of God: * Grant that we may more distinctly partake of You * on that day that has no evening in Your kingly rule.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T1|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T1|melody', 'text' : 'Be illumined.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T1|text', 'text' : 'With one voice, O Virgin, we the believers call you blest. * O rejoice, You the Lord's gate; city animate, rejoice. * Lady, rejoice, for today the light * of the resurrection from the dead of the Son * whom You have borne, has shone on us.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T2|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T2|melody', 'text' : 'Be illumined.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|Ode9T2|text', 'text' : 'Be glad and exultant, divine gate of the light. * For your Son, namely Jesus, having set within the tomb, * rose and is shining more brightly than the sun, * and He has fully illumined all the faithful, * O Lady full of the grace of God.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d00P_en_US_dedes|pePA|MM|Ode9HH1122asM1M2M3M4GMtrBMth|text', 'text' : 'For media only.'}
